ISSUE-001 | 2026-05-09
What went wrong: `pip install -e ".[dev]"` in a shared user environment reported
dependency conflicts (e.g. crewai vs installed openai/tokenizers versions).
How to avoid: Use a dedicated virtualenv for this repo
(`python -m venv .venv && source .venv/bin/activate`) before installing the
backend package.

ISSUE-002 | 2026-05-09
What went wrong: `npm install` reported moderate severity advisories in the
frontend dev dependency tree.
How to avoid: Treat as acceptable for a local scaffold; run `npm audit` before
locking production-like builds and upgrade Vite/Vitest when patches are available.

ISSUE-003 | 2026-05-09
What went wrong: Fixture path in `metrics_evaluation.py` uses
`Path(__file__).resolve().parents[3]` and will break if files are moved under
`backend/src`.
How to avoid: Prefer a single data root via environment variable or package
resources when the layout stabilises.

ISSUE-004 | 2026-05-09
What went wrong: A partially applied patch removed the `renderTable` function
signature from `frontend/src/main.ts`, breaking `npm run build` (TS1128).
How to avoid: When refactoring with patch tools, verify the edited region still
starts with complete function/block headers; run `npm run build` locally after UI edits.

================================================================================
How to run (no DB; in-memory JSON fixtures)
================================================================================
Terminal 1 — API:
  cd sdlc_with_llm/backend && python3 -m venv .venv && source .venv/bin/activate
  pip install -e ".[dev]"
  uvicorn app.main:app --reload --app-dir src --port 8000

Terminal 2 — UI (proxies /api to :8000):
  cd sdlc_with_llm/frontend && npm install && npm run dev

Open http://localhost:5173 — select a metric row to load /api/metrics/{id}/evaluation.
